    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA320-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu parattai taṉakkup pāṅkāyiṉār kēṭpa neruṅkic colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what the other woman said towards ??? so that those close to her would hear.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA320">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            viḻavu muḻantaṉṟu muḻavun tūṅkiṉ</l>
<l>            ṟevaṉkuṟit taṉaḷko leṉṟi yāyiṟ</l>
<l>            ṟaḻaiyaṇin talamvaru malkuṟ ṟeruvi</l>
<l>            ṉiḷaiyō ḷiṟanta vaṉaittaṟkup paḻaviṟa</l>
<l>            lōrik koṉṟa voruperun teruviṟ</l>
<l>            kāri pukka nērār pulampōṟ</l>
<l>            kalleṉ ṟaṉṟā lūrē yataṟkoṇṭu</l>
<l>            kāval ceṟiya māṭṭi yāytoṭi</l>
<l>            yeḻiṉmā mēṉi makaḷir</l>
<l>            viḻumān taṉartaṅ koḻunaraik kāttē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The festival is over and the drums are hung up.</l>
<l rend="indent3">If you should ask</l>
<l rend="indent3">“what did she intend?”,</l>
<l rend="indent4">when the youthful one traversed the street,</l>
<l rend="indent4">with [her] hips which swung, being adorned with foliage</l>
<l>the village really was in uproar because of the like<note place="foot">Or we read <term xml:lang="ta">vaṉaittaṟku</term> (cf. NA 29.4): "for embracing [her]"</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent3">as the field of the enemies entered by Kāri,</l>
<l rend="indent3">on the one big street where he killed Ōri of old victory.</l>
<l rend="indent3">Taking that in the women with graceful dark bodies</l>
<l rend="indent3">[and] choice bracelets closed in tightly on guard</l>
<l>[and] were excellent in guarding their husbands.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
